===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} ''[[securite]]'' < {{etyl|fro}} (French: ''[[sécurité]]'') < {{etyl|la}} ''[[securitas]]'' < {{etyl|la}} ''[[securus]]'' "[[safe]], [[secure]]".

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/sɪˈkjʊəɹəti/}}, {{SAMPA|/sI"kjU@r@ti/}}
* {{a|GenAm}} {{IPA|/səˈkjuɹ.ɪˌti}}, {{SAMPA|/sI"kjUr@ti/}}
* {{audio|En-us-security.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|securit|ies|-}}

# {{uncountable}} the condition of not being [[threaten]]ed, especially physically, psychologically, emotionally, or financially
# {{countable}} something that secures.
# an organization or department responsible for providing security by enforcing laws, rules, and regulations as well as maintaining order.
# {{legal}} something that secures the fulfillment of an obligation or law.
# {{legal}} Freedom from [[apprehension]].
# {{finance}} proof of ownership of [[stock]]s, [[bond]]s or other [[investment]] instruments.<sup>[[W:Security (finance)|W]]</sup>
# {{finance}} [[property]] temporarily [[relinquish]]ed to [[guarantee]] repayment of a [[loan]]

